h1. plugin-info

h2. Purpose

Displays detailed info about a given plug-in

h2. Examples

{code:java}
griffon plugin-info 
{code}

h2. Description

Usage: 
{code:java}
griffon plugin-info [name]
{code}

This command will display more detailed info about a given plug-in such as the author, location of documentation and so on. An example of the output of the JSecurity plug-in can be seen below:

{code}
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Information about Griffon plugin
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Name: rest      | Latest release: 0.2
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
REST client libraries
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Author: Andres Almiray
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Author's e-mail: aalmiray@users.sourceforge.net
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Find more info here: http://griffon.codehaus.org/Rest+Plugin
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
{code}
